xtent to which entrepreneurship is encouraged and shows that, while a number of factors influence enterprise, economic activities that are community-determined and provide varied opportunities to participate in achieving short-term self-sustaining strategic outcomes are particularly important.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aCommunity developmentzCanadavCase studies. 0aCommunity development. 0aEntrepreneurship. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Economy.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077357084940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773570849423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773570849/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles